cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with improving off-line writer identifications using a semi-supervised feature learning pipeline, which involves training both labeled and unlabeled data simultaneously. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and regularization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which makes cs.IR and cs.CL (Computation and Language) possible sub-categories.
